CSCI 4430: Programming Languages
PA3: Space Colonization Problem

Ryan Lin (linr2@rpi.edu)
Michael Xie (xiey3@rpi.edu)

How to run this program:

1) Compile Program.salsa and Star.salsa into Java code
2) Compile the Java code files into class files
3) Run the name server and have it listen on port 3030
4) Run each of the theaters specified in theaters.txt (ports 4040, 4041, and 4042)
5) Run the main program (pa3.Program)
  	- To run the concurrent version, run it with no arguments
	- To run the distributed version, run it with one argument called dist
	- You must create a file called input.txt in base directory containing star data
